@startuml marketplace-sequence-place-order
title Marketplace: Place an Order

actor Buyer
participant "Frontend\n(Angular)" as FE
participant "Backend API\n(Spring Boot)" as API
participant "Auth Service\n(JWT)" as AUTH
database "PostgreSQL" as DB

Buyer -> FE: Navigate to Marketplace
FE -> API: GET /api/products
API -> DB: SELECT products
DB --> API: Product list
API --> FE: 200 OK (products)
FE --> Buyer: Display product grid

Buyer -> FE: Click "Add to Cart"
FE -> API: POST /api/cart/items\n{productId, quantity}
API -> AUTH: Validate JWT token
AUTH --> API: Token valid (userId)
API -> DB: INSERT/UPDATE cart_item
DB --> API: Cart updated
API --> FE: 200 OK (cart)
FE --> Buyer: Cart badge updated

Buyer -> FE: Click "Proceed to Checkout"
FE -> API: GET /api/cart
API -> DB: SELECT cart_items
DB --> API: Cart items
API --> FE: 200 OK (cart with totals)
FE --> Buyer: Display cart summary

Buyer -> FE: Select delivery address\nand payment method
FE -> API: POST /api/orders\n{cartId, addressId, paymentMethod}
API -> AUTH: Validate JWT token
AUTH --> API: Token valid

API -> DB: BEGIN TRANSACTION
API -> DB: INSERT order
API -> DB: INSERT order_lines
API -> DB: UPDATE product stock
API -> DB: DELETE cart_items
API -> DB: COMMIT

DB --> API: Order created
API --> FE: 201 Created (orderReference)
FE --> Buyer: Order confirmation\ndisplayed with reference number
@enduml
